{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_1f3d6e19-f8f3-47d5-8173-059f306d0783","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The agent *did* encounter \"409A\" and \"$25,000\" in the transcript (52 and 51 times) — so the policy facts were in the inputs and the agent read past them, but didn't convert them into the deliverable as findings/revisions. This is the same \"exhaustive extraction\" gap from my prior memory, but here specifically about **the client's internal policy/governance document** as a controlling source. Let me confirm the task instruction and check the env case transcript to confirm the subject-property confusion is a genuine error (the agent dismissing the actual record)."}],"model":"accounts/fireworks/models/glm-5p2","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b9972eb5-9273-4ee3-8044-f92afc06f225","uuid":"ef208728-3161-4ede-a4c5-9f46ea6d16f9"}
