{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_95a90055-ba43-4ab7-ac2d-26a8d962430e","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"chatcmpl-tool-8b64a95bf64dbca1","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/.claude/memory/no-demote-and-required-components.md","content":"---\nname: no-demote-and-required-components\ndescription: After format + extraction fixes, dominant GLM failure is (A) demoting/discarding a produced document as \"not the subject / wrong property / duplicate\" so its gradable findings never reach the primary deliverable, and (B) omitting the deliverable's own required components/computations the controlling record demands. Skill edit forbids demotion and requires enumerating required sections/figures/revisions.\nmetadata:\n  type: feedback\n---\n\n**What I changed (v0, this iteration):** Extended `harness/skill/initial_skill.md` §2 with two rules and a strengthened self-check, and rewrote §4 around required-component completeness. (a) **Anti-demotion:** never reclassify a produced document as \"wrong file / not the subject property / doesn't pertain / duplicate / out of scope\" and relegate its findings to a \"secondary / appendix / do-not-rely\" section; findings from every produced doc must be first-class numbered items in the *primary* deliverable. If two docs seem to describe different subjects, surface that as its own finding but still mine BOTH fully. (b) **Governing internal docs are authority:** treat the client's own supplied policies / plan docs / board resolutions / fee agreements as controlling mandates to enforce (not background). (c) **§4 required-component & required-computation completeness:** before drafting, enumerate the deliverable's own required parts — required sections/exhibits/elements the task or governing form names, every line-item computation the record demands (carried to its specific numeric result, e.g. hours×rate, value−mortgage, % overage), and for markups every actual revision (struck/inserted text) for each flagged issue — then self-check each is present as written-out content, not \"intended/described.\" No statutes, numbers, or answer keys; all examples generic.\n\n**Failure mode targeted (from my analysis of `rollouts/`):** Format fixes from prior iterations are confirmed working — every current deliverable is full prose in the `output/` file. Two worst tasks both fail on a deeper coverage mode the prior \"exhaustive extraction\" lesson only partly hits. **environmental ESA 0.509 (26 fail):** agent wrote a thorough 502-line memo but *misidentified the subject* — treated the Greenfield Toledo ESA as primary and branded the Terravista Dayton/Millrace ESA (E1527-13; Triton Metals @2900 Millrace; Central Valley Chemical; Dayton Forge & Die; 2.3/14.7-acre NFA Parcel A; 145 Commerce Park dry cleaner; City of Dayton records) as \"misfiled different property — DO NOT RELY,\" demoting ~20 gradable findings (drum/western-yard outside NFA, private-well search + ASTM cite, vapor intrusion, pre-1987 records gap, dry-cleaner PCE plume, PCB-testing & western-yard-TCE recs, NFA scope/Bldg-2) to a secondary appendix → graded absent. **employment markup 0.538 (24 fail):** strong memo + real redline applied external law well (OWBPA, Cal 16600, DTSA) but never enforced the client's *internal settlement policy* — missed $25K/breach liquidated damages, 12-month non-compete cap (kept 18mo), mutual confidentiality, dates/title-only references, strike re-employment eligibility, 409A clause, tax indemnification, IP-assignment confirmation, board-range exceedance; policy facts appeared in transcript (409A 52×, $25K 51×) but were never converted to findings/revisions. Cross-task: capital-markets missing required S-1 *sections*; contracts missing specific negotiating *terms*; litigation/trusts/corporate-ma missing specific *dollar computations*; cyber missing immediate-action recs. Two sub-modes: (A) document demotion, (B) required-component/computation incompleteness.\n\n**Why it generalizes:** method, not memorization — \"every produced document is a source of gradable findings; never demote one\" and \"enumerate the deliverable's required components/computations and self-check each is present with its exact value\" apply to any matter regardless of practice area and read no task-specific facts, so they cannot force irrelevant artifacts (they say extract/enforce what the record warrants). This is the layer after [[exhaustive-extraction-not-thematic-essay]]: that fixed *reading* every doc and pulling verbatim; this fixes (i) not *discarding* a doc after reading it, and (ii) producing the deliverable's required *structure and computations*, not just its issue list. Builds on [[emit-deliverable-not-work-summary]] and [[deliverable-file-not-cover-note]] (format) which remain in force.\n"}}],"model":"accounts/fireworks/models/glm-5p2","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b9972eb5-9273-4ee3-8044-f92afc06f225","uuid":"2a514371-356a-4b5b-b678-515b89c8e575"}
